/target
/harmony-linux/build
/harmony-linux/dl
/harmony-linux/libvoidstar/build
/consonance/acceptance-suite/payloads/target
*.img
*.bin
!consonance/acceptance-suite/golden/*.bin
# AA-5(c) console transcripts are retained checker inputs: aa5-identity-check.py
# recomputes each console sha256 from console.bin, so a fresh checkout must carry
# them for the same-seed identity evidence to self-verify (hm-of6t F12). ~5 KiB
# ASCII each; consistency with the committed stdout hashes is what the checker gates.
!spikes/arm-altra/results/aa-5/live-20260720/**/console.bin
!spikes/arm-altra/results/aa-5/live-20260721/**/console.bin
/.claude/skills/pr-review-workspace/
.agent-prompt.md
.env
# Bring-up measurement spikes — kept on the dev box for reference, untracked from
# the tree. (The patched-KVM determinism recipe is NOT here — it lives, tracked, at
# consonance/vmm-backend/kvm-patches/.)
spikes/*
# ...with one exception, ruled by docs/ARM-ALTRA.md §Repository layout: the ARM
# vendor spike program's *apparatus* is tracked by design. Its payloads, harness,
# evidence schemas and floor checkers are arrival-day load-bearing and are reviewed
# and merged like any other code (tasks/109); only its measurement *outputs* are the
# untracked kind this rule was written for. spikes/arm-altra/.gitignore draws that
# line inside the directory.
!spikes/arm-altra/
/mutants.out
/mutants.out.old

# Run/telemetry outputs (e.g. k3s-run.*.ndjson) are data, not source.
*.ndjson
*.log

# Beads / Dolt files (added by bd init)
.dolt/
*.db
.beads-credential-key
.beads/proxieddb/
.DS_Store

# SPIKE(nested-x86): track this spike's scripts + evidence on the spike branch
# (overrides spikes/* and *.log above; last match wins)
!spikes/nested-x86
!spikes/nested-x86/**

# SPIKE(differential-lineage): tracked by design — tasks/120 requires the committed
# fixtures, generator, and benchmark report (overrides spikes/* above; last match
# wins). Build artifacts are re-ignored by the spike's own .gitignore.
!spikes/differential-lineage
!spikes/differential-lineage/**

# SPIKE(amd-epyc): the AMD vendor spike (docs/AMD-EPYC.md, tasks/123) tracks its
# apparatus AND its stage evidence (overrides spikes/* and *.log above; last match
# wins). Build artifacts are re-ignored by the spike's own .gitignore.
!spikes/amd-epyc
!spikes/amd-epyc/**
spikes/arm-altra/payloads/fixtures/*.elf
